      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Score your leave, not just your play:</span> Before confirming a move, mentally rate your leave from 1-10. If it's below 4, look for alternatives even if they score less.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The blank is sacred:</span> Never play a blank for less than 25-30 extra points over your next-best play. Its leave value is enormous — it enables bingos from almost any rack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Avoid "vowel dumps":</span> Playing 4 vowels and keeping 3 consonants sounds balanced, but you'll draw more vowels (56 in the bag vs 42 consonants). Keep 1-2 vowels to hedge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">S and blank get special treatment:</span> Hold S for plays worth 25+. Hold blanks for bingos. These tiles multiply future scoring — burning them cheaply is the #1 amateur mistake.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use the tile bag to inform leaves:</span> If 8 E's remain in the bag, keeping an E is less risky (you'll draw more vowels). If E's are depleted, keep the one you have — it's precious now.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/rack-management-basics/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
